v:4 c:$ m:portfolio role:dev x:supabase-vue
gate: OPEN

task: Wire Supabase client into Vue app with typed schema, env config, and a single composable. Backend will host: visitor analytics (page-views, room-dwell), live demo tables for "Live Showroom" room, contact-form submissions.

requires: [supabase, vue, typescript]
out:
  - app/src/lib/supabase.ts
  - app/src/composables/useSupabase.ts
  - app/src/types/database.types.ts
  - app/.env.example
  - app/.env.local (gitignored — local dev only)
  - portfolio/supabase/migrations/0001_init.sql (schema)
  - portfolio/supabase/README.md (one-page setup notes)

cmd:
  - cd app && pnpm add @supabase/supabase-js
  - cd app && pnpm add -D supabase
  - cd portfolio && pnpm dlx supabase init
  - cd portfolio && pnpm dlx supabase gen types typescript --local > app/src/types/database.types.ts

env-contract:
  - VITE_SUPABASE_URL
  - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
  (service-role key NEVER ships to client; reserved for Vercel edge functions if needed)

initial-schema (0001_init.sql):
  - table page_visits (id uuid pk, path text, ts timestamptz default now(), session_hash text)
  - table room_dwell  (id uuid pk, room text, dwell_ms int, ts timestamptz default now())
  - table contact_msgs (id uuid pk, name text, email text, body text, ts timestamptz default now())
  - RLS: anon insert-only on page_visits/room_dwell; contact_msgs insert via edge fn only.

constraints:
  - Single client instance (singleton in lib/supabase.ts).
  - useSupabase() returns typed client; never `any`.
  - No hardcoded URLs/keys outside .env.

done:
  - `import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabase'` resolves with full type inference.
  - Local `supabase start` boots; `supabase db reset` applies migration cleanly.
  - Insert from app dev console writes a row visible in Studio.
